        weight: "high",
        info: "<p><strong><code>show ip protocols</code></strong> displays <strong>all running IP routing protocols</strong> on the router, including OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, BGP. For OSPF specifically, it's a quick overview of process configuration, networks advertised, passive interfaces, and routing sources.</p><p><strong>OSPF-relevant fields in the output:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Routing Protocol is 'ospf 1':</strong> process ID.</li><li><strong>Outgoing update filter list for all interfaces is not set.</strong></li><li><strong>Incoming update filter list for all interfaces is not set.</strong></li><li><strong>Router ID X.X.X.X:</strong> active Router ID.</li><li><strong>Number of areas:</strong> count of areas this router participates in.</li><li><strong>Maximum path: N:</strong> ECMP paths (default 4; configurable with <code>maximum-paths</code>).</li><li><strong>Routing for Networks:</strong> list of network commands (if used) showing IP+wildcard+area.</li><li><strong>Routing on Interfaces Configured Explicitly:</strong> list of <code>ip ospf [pid] area [id]</code> commands (if used).</li><li><strong>Passive Interface(s):</strong> list of all passive interfaces.</li><li><strong>Routing Information Sources:</strong> list of neighbor RIDs and IPs, with last update time and AD.</li><li><strong>Distance: (default is 110):</strong> default OSPF AD.</li></ul><p><strong>Example output:</strong></p><pre>R1# show ip protocols\n*** IP Routing is NSF aware ***\nRouting Protocol is 'ospf 1'\n  Router ID 1.1.1.1\n  Number of areas in this router is 1. 1 normal 0 stub 0 nssa\n  Maximum path: 4\n  Routing for Networks:\n    10.0.0.0 0.0.0.255 area 0\n    192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0\n  Passive Interface(s):\n    GigabitEthernet0/2\n  Routing Information Sources:\n    Gateway     Distance  Last Update\n    2.2.2.2     110       00:10:15\n  Distance: (default is 110)</pre><p><strong>Quick diagnostic value:</strong> one command to see process ID, RID, networks, passive interfaces, neighbors, and AD — everything you need for 30-second OSPF sanity check.</p>",
